    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 65,
        "summary": "Ancient Israel was rejected for rejecting the Lord\u2014The Lord's people will rejoice and triumph during the Millennium.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "I am sought of them that asked not for me; I am found of them that sought me not: I said, Behold me, behold me, unto a nation that was not called by my name.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 10:20.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 63:19.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I have spread out my hands all the day unto a rebellious people, which walketh in a way that was not good, after their own thoughts;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 10:21; 2\u00a0Ne. 1:2.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A people that provoketh me to anger continually to my face; that sacrificeth in gardens, and burneth incense upon altars of brick;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:25 (24\u201325).",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Which remain among the graves, and lodge in the monuments, which eat swine's flesh, and broth of abominable things is in their vessels;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Who sit.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Which say, Stand by thyself, come not near to me; for I am holier than thou. These are a smoke in my nose, a fire that burneth all the day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 9:11 (10\u201312); Luke 18:11; Alma 31:16 (13\u201319).",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, it is written before me: I will not keep silence, but will recompense, even recompense into their bosom,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 16:18; Mosiah 12:1; D&C 1:10.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Your iniquities, and the iniquities of your fathers together, saith the Lord, which have burned incense upon the mountains, and blasphemed me upon the hills: therefore will I measure their former work into their bosom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 20:27.",
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus saith the Lord, As the new wine is found in the cluster, and one saith, Destroy it not; for a blessing is in it: so will I do for my servants' sakes, that I may not destroy them all.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0grape juice.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 18:32 (23\u201332).",
                        "start": 166,
                        "end": 169
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will bring forth a seed out of Jacob, and out of Judah an inheritor of my mountains: and mine elect shall inherit it, and my servants shall dwell there.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 69:35 (35\u201336).",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 105
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 18:9.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Sharon shall be a fold of flocks, and the valley of Achor a place for the herds to lie down in, for my people that have sought me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 2:15.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But ye are they that forsake the Lord, that forget my holy mountain, that prepare a table for that troop, and that furnish the drink offering unto that number.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Gad (an idol of fortune).",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 104
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Meni (an idol of fate).",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 158
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore will I number you to the sword, and ye shall all bow down to the slaughter: because when I called, ye did not answer; when I spake, ye did not hear; but did evil before mine eyes, and did choose that wherein I delighted not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 66:4.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 205,
                        "end": 209
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore thus saith the Lord God, Behold, my servants shall eat, but ye shall be hungry: behold, my servants shall drink, but ye shall be thirsty: behold, my servants shall rejoice, but ye shall be ashamed:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, my servants shall sing for joy of heart, but ye shall cry for sorrow of heart, and shall howl for vexation of spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 8:12.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall leave your name for a curse unto my chosen: for the Lord God shall slay thee, and call his servants by another name:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:37.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 62:2; Rev. 2:17; D&C 130:11 (10\u201311).",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That he who blesseth himself in the earth shall bless himself in the God of truth; and he that sweareth in the earth shall swear by the God of truth; because the former troubles are forgotten, and because they are hid from mine eyes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0invokes blessings in his own behalf.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0make covenants through the power of God.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For, behold, I create new heavens and a new earth: and the former shall not be remembered, nor come into mind.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Creator.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heaven.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Renewal of; Millennium.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Destiny of.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World, End of.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But be ye glad and rejoice for ever in that which I create: for, behold, I create Jerusalem a rejoicing, and her people a joy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 35:10.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will rejoice in Jerusalem, and joy in my people: and the voice of weeping shall be no more heard in her, nor the voice of crying.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 62:5.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There shall be no more thence an infant of days, nor an old man that hath not filled his days: for the child shall die an hundred years old; but the sinner being an hundred years old shall be accursed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Old Age.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:30.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall build houses, and inhabit them; and they shall plant vineyards, and eat the fruit of them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:101.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They shall not build, and another inhabit; they shall not plant, and another eat: for as the days of a tree are the days of my people, and mine elect shall long enjoy the work of their hands.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:30.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "They shall not labour in vain, nor bring forth for trouble; for they are the seed of the blessed of the Lord, and their offspring with them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Labor.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 61:9.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Eternal.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 940
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass, that before they call, I will answer; and while they are yet speaking, I will hear.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 9:26.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The wolf and the lamb shall feed together, and the lion shall eat straw like the bullock: and dust shall be the serpent's meat. They shall not hurt nor destroy in all my holy mountain, saith the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 30:12 (12\u201315).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 60:18 (17\u201322).",
                        "start": 143,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}